        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:36PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 535 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Wing, or 34
miles northeast of Bismarck, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wing and Arena.
</description>
